&quot;Her first voyage to North America began on 17 June 1860&quot;
She was converted into a cable-laying ship in 1865.
&quot;The conversion work for Great Eastern's new role consisted in the removal of funnel no. 4 and some boilers as well as great parts of the passenger rooms and saloons&quot;
